# Toolkit core

- This repo is a **bootstrap scaffold** for AI-agent environments — seed new products via `bootstrap-project` / `scripts/bootstrap-into-project.ps1` (`@docs/bootstrap-scaffold.md`).
- Docs are **AI-first → human-second**. Prefer `docs/` over prose in chat.
- Before inventing process: read `docs/cursor-official-index.md` and `AGENTS.md`.
- Any external borrow → row in `SOURCES.md` + distill in `docs/` + index update in `docs/README.md`.
- Default: link to source. Use `archive/` only when a snapshot is required.
- Keep rules/skills short; point to files (`@docs/...`, `@SOURCES.md`) instead of pasting large content.
- Project skills: `description` **на русском** (меню `/`); `name` — латиница. См. `@docs/skills-russian-descriptions.md`.
- Do not commit secrets, `.env`, or credentials.
- Prefer small, reviewable changes; descriptive branches; no force-push to `main`.
- Harness mindset: improve reusable rules/skills/docs after real tasks (compound), don't chase vanity benchmarks.
- Friction: hooks auto-log failed shells; otherwise `papercuts add` / `scripts/papercuts.ps1` (`@docs/papercuts.md`).
